<p>White-label website audit tools let agencies deliver branded audit reports that carry their own logo, colours, and contact details instead of the tool vendor's branding. This is not a vanity feature. For agencies that sell SEO services, white-label reporting is the difference between looking like a professional firm with proprietary capabilities and looking like a reseller running someone else's software.</p>

<p>The challenge is that white-label features are typically locked behind the most expensive pricing tiers of the major SEO platforms. <a href="/website-audit-tools/semrush/">Semrush</a> charges $499.95/month for white-label reports. <a href="/website-audit-tools/ahrefs/">Ahrefs</a> does not offer white labelling at all. Finding affordable white-label audit tools that produce professional-quality reports requires knowing where to look.</p>

<p>This guide reviews the best options, compares their capabilities, and provides practical advice on setting up branded reports and using audit tools as a revenue-generating service for your agency.</p>

<h2 id="what-is-white-label-auditing">What Is White Label Auditing</h2>

<p>White-label auditing means running a website audit using a third-party tool but presenting the results under your agency's brand. The client sees your logo, your colour scheme, and your contact details on the report. They do not see the name of the software that generated the data. From the client's perspective, the audit was produced by your agency's own technology.</p>

<p>This matters for several reasons. First, it reinforces your agency's brand identity. When a client receives a professionally branded report, they associate the value of the audit with your agency, not with a SaaS tool anyone could subscribe to. Second, it prevents clients from bypassing your agency by subscribing to the tool directly. If a client sees "Powered by Semrush" on every report, they may decide to buy a Semrush subscription and run the audits themselves. Third, it enables you to price your services based on the value you provide (expert interpretation and recommendations) rather than the commodity cost of the underlying data.</p>

<p>White-label auditing goes beyond simply removing the tool's branding. The best implementations include:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Custom branding:</strong> Your logo, colours, fonts, and contact details on every page of the report.</li>
  <li><strong>Custom domain dashboards:</strong> Client-facing portals hosted on your own domain (e.g., reports.youragency.com) where clients can log in and view their audit results in real time.</li>
  <li><strong>Customisable report sections:</strong> The ability to choose which sections and metrics appear in the report, tailored to each client's needs and technical understanding.</li>
  <li><strong>Automated scheduling:</strong> Reports generated and sent to clients automatically on a regular schedule, reducing manual work.</li>
  <li><strong>Custom commentary:</strong> The ability to add your own analysis, recommendations, and context alongside the automated findings.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="top-white-label-tools">Top White Label Tools</h2>

<p>Based on our testing and real-world agency use, these are the top tools that offer genuine white-label audit capabilities.</p>

<p><strong><a href="/website-audit-tools/se-ranking/">SE Ranking</a></strong> is the standout value option. White-label reporting is available on the Pro plan starting at $119/month. The reports are well-designed PDFs with full branding customisation. SE Ranking also offers a white-label client dashboard where clients can log in through a branded portal on your custom domain. The audit engine checks 120+ issues with JavaScript rendering support. For small to mid-size agencies, SE Ranking provides the best white-label value in the market.</p>

<p><strong><a href="/website-audit-tools/semrush/">Semrush</a></strong> offers white-label PDF reports on the Business plan at $499.95/month. The reports are comprehensive and professionally formatted, pulling data from across the Semrush platform (not just site audit, but also rank tracking, backlink analysis, and competitive intelligence). Semrush's white-label reports are the industry standard for agency presentations, but the price point puts them out of reach for smaller agencies.</p>

<p><strong>AgencyAnalytics</strong> is a dedicated agency reporting platform that integrates with multiple data sources including Google Analytics, Search Console, Ahrefs, Semrush, and its own built-in site audit tool. The built-in audit checks for 40+ technical issues. What makes it relevant here is the reporting layer: it pulls audit data (either from its own crawler or via API from other tools) into beautiful, fully branded reports and dashboards. Pricing starts at $79/month for the Freelancer plan with white-label on all tiers.</p>

<p><strong>Sitechecker</strong> is a dedicated website audit platform with white-label features starting at $49/month. It provides a competent audit engine (100+ checks), scheduled crawls, and branded PDF reports. The tool is less well-known than the major platforms but has built a solid reputation among agencies that need affordable white-label auditing. The reporting templates are customisable and the branded dashboard option is included on mid-tier plans.</p>

<p><strong>WebCEO</strong> is an agency-focused SEO platform that has offered white-label features since its early days. The site audit tool checks for common technical issues and produces branded reports. White-label features are available on plans starting at $99/month. WebCEO's strength is its deep customisation options for client portals, including custom CSS styling and domain mapping.</p>

<p><strong>Raven Tools</strong> (now part of TapClicks) provides white-label reporting with a site auditor included. The audit is not as comprehensive as Semrush or Ahrefs, but the reporting interface is designed specifically for agency workflows. Branded reports can be automated and scheduled for client delivery. Pricing starts at $49/month with white-label on all plans.</p>

